column35: Illumina TruSeq adaptor sequences were trimmed using cutadapt in paired-end mode (non-default parameters

column12: Cells were crosslinked with formaldehyde at a final concentration of 1% for 10 minutes at room temperature. The reaction was quenched with Glycine at a final concentration of 125mM
column13: All cell lines were cultured following the manufacturer’s recommendations
column15: Nuclear lysates were sonicated using a Branson 250 Sonifier (power setting 2, 100% duty cycle for 7 x 30-s intervals). Clarified lysates corresponding to 20 million cells were treated with 1-5ug of antibody against H3K27ac [Abcam #4729]) coupled to Protein G Dynabeads (Life Technologies #10003D, New York). The protein-DNA complexes were washed with RIPA buffer and eluted in 1% SDS TE at 65 °C, ChIP DNA sequencing libraries were generated according to Illumina DNA  TruSeq DNA Sample Preparation Kit Instructions (Illumina Part # FC-121-2001, San Diego,  CA).
column36: -m 1 --fr --chunkmbs 500 -n 2 -l 50 --mapq 40 –best) after which duplicate reads were removed using Picard MarkDuplicates
column37: -q 0.01). Peaks across all samples were combined and overlapping peaks were merged to form a single interval spanning all overlapping peaks. Peaks seen in <2 samples and peaks overlapping ENCODE blacklisted regions [https://sites.google.com/site/anshulkundaje/projects/blacklists]  were removed from further consideration

column12: Cells were crosslinked with formaldehyde at a final concentration of 1% for 10 minutes at room temperature. The reaction was quenched with Glycine at a final concentration of 125mM
